            <div type="div1" rend="DH-Heading1">
                <head>
                    <anchor type="bookmark-start" xml:id="id_discussion-and-further-research"/>Discussion and further research
                    <ptr type="bookmark-end" target="#id_discussion-and-further-research"/>
                </head>
                <p>Initial results show good and average performance on the attribution of texts and melodies, with an interesting better performance for Thibaut and Gace, our two main target authors.</p>
                <p>Yet, important work remains to be done, on one hand, to measure the relevancy of different features both for textual and musical stylometry, going beyond simple metrics. Indeed, our work results stress the necessity to go beyond bare metrics in the evaluation of supervised model training, to actually consider the precise features on which the model bases its attributions.</p>
                <p>Moreover, we aim to explore features that are at the intersection of text and music, such as recurring associations between certain musical and textual features, as well as metric patterns.</p>
